<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1859,2030]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1859,1885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is tentatively placed in the 
<emphasis box="[776,796,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">O</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[819,839,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">D</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[862,941,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">pallida</emphasis>
Group of 
<emphasis box="[1056,1215,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Dampfitrichia</emphasis>
subgenus of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kelley, R. W." pageId="1" pageNumber="27" pagination="435 - 463" refId="ref2542" refString="Kelley, R. W. (1984) Phylogeny, morphology and classification of the micro-caddisfly genus Oxyethira Eaton (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 110, 435 - 463." type="journal article" year="1984">Kelley (1984)</bibRefCitation>
due to segment VII being without a ventral apicomesal process; segment VIII venter being shallowly excised apically and without dorsolateral processes; segment IX having its venter pointed anteriorly and protruding to the anterior end of segment VII; the inferior appendages distinct, short; and the aedeagus lacking a titillator and having a distal process. The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Neto &amp; Passos, 2022" authorityName="Neto &amp; Passos" authorityYear="2022" box="[474,687,2004,2030]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiquitaia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[474,687,2004,2030]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">Oxyethira jiquitaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[693,782,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[693,782,2004,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint 1974" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[1003,1279,2004,2030]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longissima">
<emphasis box="[1003,1157,2004,2030]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="27">O. longissima</emphasis>
Flint 
<quantity box="[1223,1279,2004,2030]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.01396" pageId="1" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="1974.0">1974</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the general shape of the inferior appendages, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint 1974" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[591,895,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrosterna">
<emphasis box="[591,768,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">O. macrosterna</emphasis>
Flint 
<quantity box="[839,895,151,177]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.01396" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="1974.0">1974</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the general shape of the subgenital process. However, in the new species, segment IX in lateral view extends a bit further than the anterior margin of segment VII, but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[276,431,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longissima">
<emphasis box="[276,431,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">O. longissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[486,661,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Oxyethira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrosterna">
<emphasis box="[486,661,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">O. macrosterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, segment IX is much more prolonged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,258,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,409,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Male</emphasis>
. Length of each forewing 1.55 mm (n = 6). Head unmodified, with 3 ocelli; antennae broken and lost. Tibial spurs 1,3,4. Dorsum of head dark brown with pale yellow setae; thorax dark brown dorsally, light brown ventrally, with pale yellow setae dorsally; leg segments with light brown setae. Forewing venation typical of the genus, covered with fine yellow setae and small scattered patches of dark brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,384,402,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Male Genitalia.</emphasis>
Abdominal segment VII annular, without apicomesal ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1263,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Segment VIII with posteroventral margins sinuous in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[763,856,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view anterior margin slightly concave, posterior margin difficult to define (
<figureCitation box="[560,648,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); in ventral view anterior margin sinuous, posterior margin shallowly excised mesally, produced into two truncate lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[806,894,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Segment IX in lateral view tapering anteriorly and withdrawn into segments VII–VIII extending slightly beyond anterior margin of segment VII, with truncated process at dorsal posterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[556,647,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view anterodorsal margin shallowly excised mesally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); in ventral and dorsal views lateral margins tapering anteriorly to acute base (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1198,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Figs 1B, 1C</figureCitation>
). Tergum X in lateral view membranous, posterior margin blunt (
<figureCitation box="[649,751,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Figs. 1A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view posterior margin almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[1332,1422,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages sclerotized, in lateral view with acute apex directed posterodorsad (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1215,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
, ia); in ventral view fused mesally, produced into pair of almost-rectangular lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[941,1029,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
, ia). Subgenital process sclerotized, in lateral view robust, curving posteroventrad (
<figureCitation box="[697,789,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
, sg), with elongate mesal process, directed caudad, and narrow apically (
<figureCitation box="[341,429,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
, mp); in dorsal view with triangular process produced apicomesally (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1288,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
, sg). Bilobed processes in ventral view widely separated, digitate and each with spine-like apical seta (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1256,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
, bp). Phallus in lateral view with tubular basal half, membranous apical half, ventrally with elongate, slender, and pointed apex, with basal keel-shaped process (
<figureCitation box="[521,611,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
, vp); internally with long and sclerotized ejaculatory duct acute at apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,248,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[161,1421,468,1689]" captionTargetId="figure-61@1.[151,1436,453,1694]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Oxyethira jiquitaia sp. nov. male genitalia. 1A, left lateral; 1B, dorsal; 1C, ventral; 1D, phallus, left lateral. bp = bilobed process, ed = ejaculatory duct, ia = inferior appendage (paired), mp = mesal process of subgenital plate, sg = subgenital plate, vp = ventral process of phallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911223/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
, ed).
</paragraph>
