<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Etymology.</emphasis>
The term “jiquitaia,” a noun used in apposition, refers to the oral word used by inhabitants of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,306,1195,1221]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Roraima state</collectingRegion>
to designate a hot food powder made of a sun dried and ground pepper.
</paragraph>
